---
import SectionWrapper from '../SectionWrapper.astro';
---
<SectionWrapper id="faq" theme="light">
  <!-- Section label -->
  <p class="section-label section-label--light">// 09 FAQ</p>

  <!-- Headline -->
  <h2 class="faq-headline">Common concerns. Direct answers.</h2>

  <!-- FAQ container -->
  <div class="faq-container" data-animate>
    <!-- Q1 -->
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary class="faq-question">What exactly is a 'business operating system'?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>It's the three things every business needs to work without the owner holding them together manually: a clear message that explains what you do to a stranger, a website that converts visitors into leads, and tools that connect to each other. Most businesses have all three. None of them were built to work together. That's the problem I fix.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <!-- Q2 -->
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary class="faq-question">Do you use WordPress, Webflow, or Squarespace?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>No. I write custom code. You can update your own content without calling me, and the code is permanently yours. No platform holds it hostage. No monthly fee to maintain access to your own site.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <!-- Q3 -->
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary class="faq-question">How long does a project take?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>Simple marketing sites ship in under a week. Email automation takes two to four weeks. App projects start at two weeks and expand with complexity. I don't quote a timeline before I understand the problem. The diagnostic tells us which situation you're in. Timeline follows scope, and scope follows diagnosis.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <!-- Q4 -->
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary class="faq-question">What's in the Handoff Package?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>Full codebase. Hosting credentials. CMS instructions. The original Problem Statement. Everything you need to run your operating system without me. Nothing is locked to MAX.EXE.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <!-- Q5 -->
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary class="faq-question">I've hired people before and it didn't work. Why would this be different?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>Most projects fail because the answer was sold before the question was asked. Someone built what they thought you needed instead of diagnosing what was actually broken. I start with a written Problem Statement, verified by you in plain language, before a dollar is spent on development. You know exactly what you're getting before I build it.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <!-- Q6 -->
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary class="faq-question">I already have a website. Do I need to start over?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>Not necessarily. I map what exists, find what's broken, and build around your actual situation. Sometimes the site just needs new copy and structure. Sometimes it needs a rebuild. The diagnostic tells us which.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <!-- Q7 -->
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary class="faq-question">I'm just starting my business. Is this for me?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>Yes. Starting with a complete operating system is easier than building one piece at a time and trying to connect them later. The diagnostic routes you to the right starting point.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <!-- Q8 -->
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary class="faq-question">How are you different from a freelancer or agency?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>Everything ships documented. You can run your own system without me after launch. Most freelancers and agencies don't build that way because it removes the dependency that keeps you calling them back. I build for your independence because I'd rather earn future work by being the best option, not the only option.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <!-- Q9 -->
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary class="faq-question">I'm not technical. Will I understand what you're building?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>The Problem Statement is written in plain language before any code starts. If it doesn't make sense to you, that's on me, not you. You don't need to understand the code. You need to understand what it does for your business. That's what the Problem Statement covers.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <!-- Q10 -->
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary class="faq-question">What does 'AI for small business' actually mean here?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>It starts with one question: what task do you do by hand every week that a machine should handle? Intake, follow-up, FAQs, appointment scheduling. I find that task, build around your data, and train it in your voice. You approve every output before anything goes live.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <!-- Q11 -->
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary class="faq-question">What does hosting cost after launch?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>I deploy to Cloudflare or Vercel. Both are under $20 per month, often free for static sites. You get full credentials before handoff. Nothing is billed through me after launch.</p>
      </div>
    </details>
  </div>
</SectionWrapper>

<style>
  /* Headline - Geist Sans */
  .faq-headline {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--step-4);
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-snug);
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
    max-width: var(--measure-wide);
  }

  /* FAQ container */
  .faq-container {
    max-width: var(--measure-normal);
  }

  /* Accordion items */
  .faq-item {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-muted);
  }

  .faq-item:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  /* Question trigger */
  .faq-question {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    width: 100%;
    font-family: var(--font-pixel);
    font-size: var(--step-0);
    color: var(--primary);
    min-height: 44px;
    padding: var(--space-5) 0;
    padding-right: var(--space-10);
    cursor: pointer;
    list-style: none;
    position: relative;
  }

  /* Remove native disclosure marker */
  .faq-question::-webkit-details-marker,
  .faq-question::marker {
    display: none;
    content: '';
  }

  /* Custom +/- indicator */
  .faq-question::after {
    content: '+';
    position: absolute;
    right: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--step-1);
    color: var(--primary);
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .faq-item[open] .faq-question::after {
    content: '\2212';
  }

  /* Answer content */
  .faq-answer {
    padding: 0 0 var(--space-6) 0;
  }

  .faq-answer p {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--step-0);
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    max-width: var(--measure-normal);
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .faq-headline {
      font-size: var(--step-3);
    }

    .faq-question {
      font-size: var(--step--1);
      padding-right: var(--space-8);
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .faq-headline {
      font-size: var(--step-2);
    }

    .faq-question {
      font-size: var(--step--1);
    }
  }
</style>
